+# Spec: Status Filter for Tasks API
+
+## Problem
+The public tasks API (`GET /api/tasks`) supports filtering by difficulty but not by status. Consumers need to filter tasks by their lifecycle status (draft, review, published).
+
+## Solution
+Add a `status` query parameter to `GET /api/tasks` that filters tasks by their `status` field.
+
+## Requirements
+1. `status` query parameter accepts values: `draft`, `review`, `published`
+2. Invalid status values are silently ignored (return all tasks, not zero)
+3. Existing `difficulty` filtering continues to work unchanged
+4. `status` and `difficulty` filters can be combined
+5. Focused API route tests cover the new behavior
+
+## Non-Goals
+- No changes to benchmark result data, docs, or report files
+- No changes to authentication or rate limiting
+- No changes to the task schema or data store
